\ul To set up a computer with the CellProfiler directory cvs'd (for PC):\
\ulnone Download and install with all options TortoiseSVN from http://tortoisesvn.tigris.org/\
Checkout new copy entering: http://svn.csail.mit.edu/cellprofiler/CellProfiler/trunk\
This will create a trunk/CellProfiler directory on your computer. All commands can now be done by right clicking the folder/file of interest (ignore all the SVN command line instructions below).\
In Matlab, be sure to set the path to include this new folder & its subfolders as follows:\
File-->Set Path --> Add with Subfolders--> choose CellProfiler folder --> save\
You can save your username/password by checking the box that appears after your first update.\
\
\ul To set up a computer with the CellProfiler directory cvs'd (for Mac):\
\ulnone Download and install the latest Mac os X package version at http://metissian.com/projects/macosx/subversion/     (as of Sept 2005, this is version 1.2.3  up)\
After installation finishes, open the terminal and cd to /Users/youraccount/ (and whatever subfolder you want CellProfiler to be installed in), and type:\
export PATH=$PATH:/usr/local/bin\
The first time you are settings this up, type the following to check out CellProfiler to your local computer:\
svn co http://svn.csail.mit.edu/cellprofiler/CellProfiler/trunk\
This will create a trunk/CellProfiler directory on your computer. At that point you can edit, commit changes, etc. (see commands below).\
In Matlab, be sure to set the path to include this new folder & its subfolders as follows:\
File-->Set Path --> Add with Subfolders--> choose CellProfiler folder --> save\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural
\cf0 If you get an error message says that the pathdef.m can't be saved , you have to change the permissions for the Matlab folder first. To do that (in Finder) right click on MatLab folder  --> Get Info --> change the owner to yourself. Close the Get Info window. Reopen the Get Info for MatLab folder, change the owner to system(root), be sure to allow group and others to read and write. (The GetInfo tool in Finder is a little buggy - that's why you have to open/reopen. You can also chmod using the command line if you know how).\
