\ul SVN commands\ulnone \
Overall, to reconcile your local copy with the central svn copy, first update yourself (retrieve other people's changes), then check for differences between your version and the central version (optional), then commit (submit your changes to the central version).\
\
To run any svn commands, in terminal, change to the directory where CellProfiler resides.  You may need to type this command if it can't find the SVN program:\
export $PATH=PATH:/usr/local/bin\
\ul \
To update (get up-to-date code):\ulnone  svn update\
\
\ul To show what differences exist between your copy and the last central copy you checked out: \ulnone svn diff\
\
\ul To show what differences exist between particular revision numbers\ulnone \
svn diff -r REVNUMBER REVNUMBER  (providing only one revision number will compare to your locally modified copy, I think)\
\
\ul If you get "it is in the way" errors:\
\ulnone If you don't have any local modifications that you need to commit, just remove the parent directory altogether and then svn update -d to restore a fresh version of the folder.\
\
\ul To obtain revision numbers:\
\ulnone svn log Filename.m\
\
\ul To commit changes one by one: (\ulnone leave off the specific filename to commit all)\
svn commit -m "Description of this change" filename.m\
\ul \
To add a file which is not already in the central copy:\ulnone \
svn add filename.m\
(this only adds it to your local svn list, not the central one, so the next step is to svn commit)\
\
\ul To lock a file so that only you can commit to it:\ulnone \
svn admin -l filename\
When you check in a new version, the lock will be unlocked by default,\
so you'll have to do it again.\
\
\ul To remove a file from the repository:\
\ulnone svn update filename.m\
move the file from the directory\
svn remove filename.m\
svn commit filename.m\
\
\ul To rename a file without losing all the SVN history:\
\ulnone Of course you can svn add with the new name and svn remove the old name, but this will lose all the SVN history.  So instead, you need to go to the computer which has the repository: \
cp oldfile.c,v newfile.c,v\
now go to your working directory and do a svn update; newfile.c will appear as a new file. Now you can svn delete oldfile.c and commit.\
\ul To see a list of all files and their status:\
\ulnone svn status}